      <div class="feature-columns">
        <article>
          <p class="feature-number">01</p>
          <h3>Production foundation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Custom email-based user model</li>
            <li>Registration, login, logout and protected dashboard</li>
            <li>PostgreSQL across local, test and production settings</li>
            <li>Database-aware health endpoint</li>
            <li>pytest, Ruff and GitHub Actions CI</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article>
          <p class="feature-number">02</p>
          <h3>Structured question library</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Technical, behavioural and repository-debugging question types</li>
            <li>Type-specific create, edit and detail experiences</li>
            <li>Private user-owned libraries</li>
            <li>Search and filters for type, status and difficulty</li>
            <li>Progressive technical-answer and diagnosis reveal</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article>
          <p class="feature-number">03</p>
          <h3>Bulk import and review</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Pasted text, TXT, Markdown, CSV, DOCX and text-based PDF input</li>
            <li>Resumable review batches and editable generated titles</li>
            <li>Per-item type overrides and duplicate detection</li>
            <li>Transactional, idempotent creation</li>
            <li>Needs-notes and mark-ready validation workflows</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Architecture</p>
        <h2>Decisions made for clarity and controlled growth.</h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="decision-list">
      <div>
        <h3>Modular Django monolith</h3>
        <p>Clear domain boundaries without introducing distributed-system complexity before the product requires it.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>PostgreSQL from the beginning</h3>
        <p>One relational data model across local, test and production environments, with no application SQLite fallback.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Concrete base question with typed children</h3>
        <p>Shared behaviour remains central while each interview format stores and presents its own relevant detail.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Deterministic logic before AI</h3>
        <p>Study planning and review behaviour will remain visible, explainable and testable independently of future AI features.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container">
    <div class="development-panel">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Development workflow</p>
        <h2>AI-assisted, verification-led delivery.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>
        I use AI to challenge architecture choices, turn agreed decisions into implementation plans,
        generate test ideas, investigate bugs and improve documentation. I retain ownership of the product rules,
        architecture, trade-offs and acceptance criteria, then review the code, trace the behaviour and run the tests
        before accepting a change.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section container">
    <div class="section-heading">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Next scope</p>
        <h2>Planned product layers.</h2>
      </div>
      <p>These features are not presented as part of the current release.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="roadmap-list">
      <div>
        <span>01</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Practice and review history</h3>
          <p>Practice sessions, confidence, mistakes, review records and curriculum coverage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>02</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Deterministic Focus Engine</h3>
          <p>Recommendations based on interview stage, dates, weak areas, available time and prior reviews.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span>03</span>
        <div>
          <h3>Grounded retrieval</h3>
